# Uruguay Visa for Taiwanese Citizens — Applying in Buenos Aires

## Required Documents
1. Taiwan passport (valid 6+ months, must be signed)
2. 1 passport-sized photo (2-inch, taken within 6 months)
3. Cash in Argentine Pesos for the visa fee

## Fee
~54 USD equivalent in Argentine Pesos (pesos only, official rate on the day)

## Process
1. Walk in to the Uruguayan Embassy in Buenos Aires (walk-ins work despite website showing long appointment waits)
2. Submit passport + photo, answer basic questions (purpose, duration, employment, etc.)
3. They process and email you when approved (a few days)
4. Return to pick up visa, pay fee in cash, get passport stamped

## Visa Details
- Must be used within 60 days of issuance
- Valid for 90 days, multiple entries
- Passport is not confiscated during processing

## Consulate in Rosario
- Address: Av. Belgrano 958, S2000 Rosario, Santa Fe
- Phone: +54 341 424 6860
- Email: cgrosario@mrree.gub.uy
- Hours: Mon-Fri 9:00-15:00
- Appointment: Email cgrosario@mrree.gub.uy with required documents attached. They'll reply with a date/time.
- Apply at least 40 days before your trip

## Embassy in Buenos Aires (alternative)
- Website: https://embajadadeluruguay.com.ar/
- Address: Arenales 1392, Buenos Aires
- Phone: +54 11 6009-5040
- Email: cdbuenosaires@mrree.gub.uy
- Hours: Mon-Fri 9:00-16:00
- Appointments: https://turnosconsulado.com.ar/

## Tips
- No proof of accommodation or flight tickets needed
- Bring extra copies of passport info page
- Only pesos accepted, no USD
- Embassy is in Buenos Aires, 2nd floor — tell security you're there for a visa
